pwAtmMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for pseudowire emulation of ATM over Packet Switched Networks (PSNs). This MIB supplements the PW-STD-MIB module. The PW-STD-MIB contains structures and MIB associations generic to pseudowire (PW) emulation. PW-specific MIBs (such as this) contain config and stats for specific PW types. pwAtmOutboundTable.name: pwAtmOutboundTable
pwAtmOutboundTable.description: This table specifies the information for an ATM PW to be carried over the PSN in the outbound direction. An entry is created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to one of the following: atmAal5SduVcc(2), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), atmCell1to1Vpc(13) or atmAal5PduVcc(14), or atmTransparent(3).

pwAtmOutboundEntry.name: pwAtmOutboundEntry
pwAtmOutboundEntry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM PW that needs to be adapted and carried over the PSN. This table is indexed by pwIndex from pwTable. Unless otherwise specified, all writeable objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation in the generic pwTable, and values must persist after reboot.

pwAtmOutboundAtmIf.name: pwAtmOutboundAtmIf
pwAtmOutboundAtmIf.description: The ATM Interface that receives cells from the ATM network.

pwAtmOutboundVpi.name: pwAtmOutboundVpi
pwAtmOutboundVpi.description: VPI value of this ATM PW. The value may indicate the translated value when egress generates new VPI.

pwAtmOutboundVci.name: pwAtmOutboundVci
pwAtmOutboundVci.description: VCI value of this ATM PW. The value may indicate the translated value when egress generates new VCI.

pwAtmOutboundTrafficParamDescr.name: pwAtmOutboundTrafficParamDescr
pwAtmOutboundTrafficParamDescr.description: This object represents a pointer to an ATM traffic-parameter-specific row in either a private or standard table that will be employed while receiving cells from the ATM network. This row should contain a set of self-consistent ATM traffic parameters including the ATM traffic service category. A value of 0.0 indicates Best Effort.

pwAtmOutboundRowStatus.name: pwAtmOutboundRowStatus
pwAtmOutboundRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, modify, or delete a row in this table. Unless otherwise specified, all writeable objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation as explained in the pwAtmOutboundEntry.

pwAtmInboundTable.name: pwAtmInboundTable
pwAtmInboundTable.description: This table specifies the information for an ATM PW in the inbound direction.

pwAtmInboundEntry.name: pwAtmInboundEntry
pwAtmInboundEntry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM PW that needs to be sent into the ATM network after reconstructing cells from packets received from a PSN. This table is indexed by pwIndex from pwTable. An entry is created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to one of the following: atmAal5SduVcc(2), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), atmCell1to1Vpc(13), atmAal5PduVcc(14), or atmTransparent(3). Unless otherwise specified, all writeable objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation in the generic pwTable, and values must persist after reboot.

pwAtmInboundAtmIf.name: pwAtmInboundAtmIf
pwAtmInboundAtmIf.description: The ATM Interface that sends cells into the ATM network after reconstructing cells from packets received from a PSN.

pwAtmInboundVpi.name: pwAtmInboundVpi
pwAtmInboundVpi.description: VPI value of this ATM PW. If the pwType is atmTransparent, then the value will be set to zero.

pwAtmInboundVci.name: pwAtmInboundVci
pwAtmInboundVci.description: VCI value of this ATM PW. If the pwType is atmTransparent, atmCell1to1Vpc, or atmCellNto1Vpc, then the value will be set to zero.

pwAtmInboundTrafficParamDescr.name: pwAtmInboundTrafficParamDescr
pwAtmInboundTrafficParamDescr.description: This object represents a pointer to an ATM traffic-parameter- specific row in either a private or standard table that will be employed while transmitting into the ATM network. This table contains a set of self-consistent ATM traffic parameters including the ATM traffic service category. A value of 0.0 indicates Best Effort.

pwAtmInboundRowStatus.name: pwAtmInboundRowStatus
pwAtmInboundRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, modify, or delete a row in this table. Unless otherwise specified, all writeable objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation as explained in the pwAtmInboundEntry.

pwAtmCfgTable.name: pwAtmCfgTable
pwAtmCfgTable.description: This table specifies generic information for an ATM PW to be carried over PSN in any mode.

pwAtmCfgEntry.name: pwAtmCfgEntry
pwAtmCfgEntry.description: This table contains a set of parameters for the ATM PW that needs to be adapted and carried over the PSN. This table is indexed by pwIndex from pwTable. An entry is created for every new ATM type associated pwIndex in the pwTable. Unless otherwise specified, all read-write objects in this table MAY be changed when the PW is defined as not active, and all RW objects values must persist after reboot.

pwAtmCfgMaxCellConcatenation.name: pwAtmCfgMaxCellConcatenation
pwAtmCfgMaxCellConcatenation.description: The maximum number of ATM cells that can be concatenated into one PW packet towards the PSN. In a non-LDP or other signaling protocol environment, this object MAY be changed at anytime, but traffic might be interrupted; otherwise, it may be changed when PW is not active.

pwAtmCfgFarEndMaxCellConcatenation.name: pwAtmCfgFarEndMaxCellConcatenation
pwAtmCfgFarEndMaxCellConcatenation.description: The maximum number of ATM cells that can be concatenated into one PW packet towards PSN as reported by the far end. If there is no LDP in use, the object will either return a value of 0 or allow setting it for calculating protocol overhead.

pwAtmCfgTimeoutMode.name: pwAtmCfgTimeoutMode
pwAtmCfgTimeoutMode.description: This object determines whether or not a packet can be transmitted to the PSN based on timeout expiration for collecting cells. The actual handling of the timeout is implementation-specific; as such, this object may be changed at any time under proper consideration of the traffic interruption effect.

pwAtmClpQosMapping.name: pwAtmClpQosMapping
pwAtmClpQosMapping.description: This object indicates whether the Cell Loss Priority (CLP) bits should be considered when setting the value in the Quality-of-Service fields of the encapsulating protocol (e.g., EXP fields of the MPLS Label Stack). Selecting True allows the drop precedence to be preserved across the PSN. In transparent cell transport, the value of this object MUST be false(2); in other cases, it can be changed at any time.

pwAtmOutboundNto1Table.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1Table
pwAtmOutboundNto1Table.description: This table specifies the information for an ATM PW to be carried over the PSN in the outbound direction. Up to N entries can be created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to: atmCellNto1Vcc(9) or atmCellNto1Vpc(10). An entry can be created only when the VP/VC are known. A single entry will be created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to one of the following: atmCell1to1Vcc(12), atmCell1to1Vpc(13), atmAal5PduVcc(14), atmAal5SduVcc(2), or atmTransparent(3).

pwAtmOutboundNto1Entry.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1Entry
pwAtmOutboundNto1Entry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM PW that needs to be adapted and carried over PSN. This table is indexed by pwIndex from pwTable and the ATM interface with VPL/VCLs. In atmTransparent(3), Vpi and VCi will be 0xFFFF during set operation. Unless otherwise specified, all read-create objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation and SHOULD remain unchanged after reboot.

pwAtmOutboundNto1AtmIf.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1AtmIf
pwAtmOutboundNto1AtmIf.description: The ATM Interface that receives cells from the ATM network.

pwAtmOutboundNto1Vpi.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1Vpi
pwAtmOutboundNto1Vpi.description: VPI value of this ATM PW. In atmTransparent(3), Vpi will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF.

pwAtmOutboundNto1Vci.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1Vci
pwAtmOutboundNto1Vci.description: VCI value of this ATM PW. In atmTransparent(3), or the VP case, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF.

pwAtmOutboundNto1RowStatus.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1RowStatus
pwAtmOutboundNto1RowStatus.description: This object is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

pwAtmOutboundNto1TrafficParamDescr.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1TrafficParamDescr
pwAtmOutboundNto1TrafficParamDescr.description: This object represents a pointer to an ATM traffic-parameter- specific row in either private or standard table that will be employed while receiving cells from the ATM network. This table should contain a set of self-consistent ATM traffic parameters including the ATM traffic service category. A value of 0.0 indicates Best Effort.

pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVpi.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVpi
pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVpi.description: The egress-generated VPI value of this ATM PW. The entry is valid for PW type of atmCellNto1Vcc(9), atmCellNto1Vpc(10), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), or atmCell1to1Vpc(13). In other types, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF. Value MAY be changed when the PW is defined as not active.

pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVci.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVci
pwAtmOutboundNto1MappedVci.description: The egress-generated VCI value of this ATM PW. The entry is valid for PW type of atmCellNto1Vcc(9), atmCellNto1Vpc(10), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), or atmCell1to1Vpc(13. In the VP case or other types, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF. Value MAY be changed when the PW is defined as not active.

pwAtmInboundNto1Table.name: pwAtmInboundNto1Table
pwAtmInboundNto1Table.description: This table specifies the information for an ATM PW to be carried over PSN in the Inbound direction. Up to N entries can be created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to: atmCellNto1Vcc(9) or atmCellNto1Vpc(10). An entry can be created only when the VP/VC are known. A single entry will be created in this table for every entry in the pwTable with a pwType equal to one of the following: atmCell1to1Vcc(12), atmCell1to1Vpc(13), atmAal5PduVcc(14), atmAal5SduVcc(2), or atmTransparent(3).

pwAtmInboundNto1Entry.name: pwAtmInboundNto1Entry
pwAtmInboundNto1Entry.description: A row in this table represents an ATM PW that needs to be adapted and carried over PSN. This table is indexed by pwIndex from pwTable and the ATM interface with VPL/VCLs. In atmTransparent(3), Vpi and VCi will be 0xFFFF during set operation. Unless otherwise specified, all Read-Create objects in this table MUST NOT be changed after row activation and SHOULD remain unchanged after reboot.

pwAtmInboundNto1AtmIf.name: pwAtmInboundNto1AtmIf
pwAtmInboundNto1AtmIf.description: The ATM Interface that receives cells from the ATM network.

pwAtmInboundNto1Vpi.name: pwAtmInboundNto1Vpi
pwAtmInboundNto1Vpi.description: VPI value of this ATM PW. In atmTransparent(3), Vpi will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF.

pwAtmInboundNto1Vci.name: pwAtmInboundNto1Vci
pwAtmInboundNto1Vci.description: VCI value of this ATM PW. In atmTransparent(3), or the VP case, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF.

pwAtmInboundNto1RowStatus.name: pwAtmInboundNto1RowStatus
pwAtmInboundNto1RowStatus.description: This object is used to create, modify, or delete a row in this table.

pwAtmInboundNto1TrafficParamDescr.name: pwAtmInboundNto1TrafficParamDescr
pwAtmInboundNto1TrafficParamDescr.description: This object represents a pointer to an ATM traffic-parameter- specific row in either a private or standard table that will be employed while receiving cells from the ATM network. This table should contain a set of self-consistent ATM traffic parameters including the ATM traffic service category. A value of 0.0 indicates Best Effort.

pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVpi.name: pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVpi
pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVpi.description: The generated VPI value of this ATM PW. The entry is valid for PW type of atmCellNto1Vcc(9), atmCellNto1Vpc(10), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), or atmCell1to1Vpc(13). In other types, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF. Value MAY be changed when the PW is defined as not active.

pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVci.name: pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVci
pwAtmInboundNto1MappedVci.description: The generated VCI value of this ATM PW. The entry is valid for PW type of atmCellNto1Vcc(9), atmCellNto1Vpc(10), atmCell1to1Vcc(12), or atmCell1to1Vpc(13. In the VP case or other types, the value will be the equivalent of 0xFFFF. Value MAY be changed when the PW is defined as not active.

pwAtmPerfCurrentTable.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentTable
pwAtmPerfCurrentTable.description: The current 15-minute interval counts are in this table. This table provides performance information per ATM PW.

pwAtmPerfCurrentEntry.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentEntry
pwAtmPerfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every pwAtmCfgTable entry. After 15 minutes, the contents of this table entry are copied to a new entry in the pwAtmPerfInterval table and the counts in this entry are reset to zero.

pwAtmPerfCurrentMissingPkts.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentMissingPkts
pwAtmPerfCurrentMissingPkts.description: Number of missing packets (as detected via control word sequence number gaps).

pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsReOrder.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsReOrder
pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsReOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via control word sequence number), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations may not support this feature.

pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsMisOrder.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsMisOrder
pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsMisOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of order (via control word sequence numbers).

pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsTimeout.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsTimeout
pwAtmPerfCurrentPktsTimeout.description: Number of packets transmitted due to timeout expiration while attempting to collect cells.

pwAtmPerfCurrentUnknownCells.name: pwAtmPerfCurrentUnknownCells
pwAtmPerfCurrentUnknownCells.description: Number of cells received from the PSN with unknown VPI or VCI values. This object is relevant only in N:1 mode.

pwAtmPerfIntervalTable.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalTable
pwAtmPerfIntervalTable.description: This table provides performance information per ATM PW similar to the pwAtmPerfCurrentTable above. However, these counts represent historical 15 minute intervals. Typically, this table will have a maximum of 96 entries for a 24 hour period.

pwAtmPerfIntervalEntry.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalEntry
pwAtmPerfIntervalEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every pwAtmPerfCurrentEntry that is 15 minutes old. The contents of the Current entry are copied to the new entry here. The Current entry then resets its counts to zero for the next current 15 minute interval.

pwAtmPerfIntervalNumber.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalNumber
pwAtmPerfIntervalNumber.description: A number (normally between 1 and 96 to cover a 24 hour period) that identifies the interval for which the set of statistics is available. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1. The minimum range of N is 1 through 4. The default range is 1 through 32. The maximum value of N is 96.

pwAtmPerfIntervalValidData.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalValidData
pwAtmPerfIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

pwAtmPerfIntervalDuration.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalDuration
pwAtmPerfIntervalDuration.description: The duration of a particular interval in seconds. Adjustments in the system's time-of-day clock, may cause the interval to be greater or less than the normal value. Therefore, this actual interval value is provided.

pwAtmPerfIntervalMissingPkts.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalMissingPkts
pwAtmPerfIntervalMissingPkts.description: Number of missing packets (as detected via control word sequence number gaps).

pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsReOrder.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsReOrder
pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsReOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via control word sequence number), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations may not support this feature.

pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsMisOrder.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsMisOrder
pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsMisOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of order (via control word sequence numbers).

pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsTimeout.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsTimeout
pwAtmPerfIntervalPktsTimeout.description: Number of packets transmitted due to timeout expiration.

pwAtmPerfIntervalUnknownCells.name: pwAtmPerfIntervalUnknownCells
pwAtmPerfIntervalUnknownCells.description: Number of cells received from the PSN with unknown VPI or VCI values. This object is relevant only in N:1 mode.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalTable.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalTable
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalTable.description: This table provides performance information per ATM PW similar to the pwAtmPerfIntervalTable above. However, these counters represent historical one-day intervals up to one full month.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalEntry.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalEntry
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalEntry.description: An entry is created in this table by the agent for every entry in the pwAtmCfgTable table.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalNumber.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalNumber
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalNumber.description: The number of intervals, where 1 indicates current day measured period and 2 and above indicate previous days, respectively.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalValidData.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalValidData
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalValidData.description: This object indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalDuration.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalDuration
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalDuration.description: The duration of a particular interval in seconds. Adjustments in the system's time-of-day clock may cause the interval to be greater or less than the normal value. Therefore, this actual interval value is provided.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalMissingPkts.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalMissingPkts
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalMissingPkts.description: Number of missing packets (as detected via control word sequence number gaps).

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsReOrder.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsReOrder
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsReOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via control word sequence number), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations may not support this feature.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsMisOrder.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsMisOrder
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsMisOrder.description: Number of packets detected out of order (via control word sequence numbers) and that could not be re-ordered.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsTimeout.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsTimeout
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalPktsTimeout.description: Number of packets transmitted due to timeout expiration.

pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalUnknownCells.name: pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalUnknownCells
pwAtmPerf1DayIntervalUnknownCells.description: Number of cells received from the PSN with unknown VPI or VCI values. This object is relevant only in N:1 mode.

pwAtmCompliance.name: pwAtmCompliance
pwAtmCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support ATM PW.

pwAtmCfgGroup.name: pwAtmCfgGroup
pwAtmCfgGroup.description: Collection of objects for basic ATM PW configuration.

pwAtmPerfGroup.name: pwAtmPerfGroup
pwAtmPerfGroup.description: Collection of objects for basic ATM PW Performance.

pwAtmOutbound1to1Group.name: pwAtmOutbound1to1Group
pwAtmOutbound1to1Group.description: Collection of objects for basic 1:1 ATM PW outbound configuration.

pwAtmInbound1to1Group.name: pwAtmInbound1to1Group
pwAtmInbound1to1Group.description: Collection of objects for basic 1:1 ATM PW inbound configuration.

pwAtmOutboundNto1Group.name: pwAtmOutboundNto1Group
pwAtmOutboundNto1Group.description: Collection of objects for N:1, 1:1, or transparent ATM PW outbound configuration.

pwAtmInboundNto1Group.name: pwAtmInboundNto1Group
pwAtmInboundNto1Group.description: Collection of objects for N:1, 1:1, or transparent ATM PW inbound configuration.
